
1/4 cup oil
2 medium potatoes, peeled and quartered
2 large carrots, peeled and cubed
1 small onion, peeled and chopped
3 cloves garlic, peeled and minced
1 thumb ginger, peeled and minced
4 lbs chicken, cut
1 Tbsp fish sauce
2 cups coconut milk
1 cup water
1/2 green bell pepper
1/2 red bell pepper
2 Tbsp curry powder


In wide pan over medium heat, heat oil.
Add potatoes; cook 2 to 3 minutes
Remove potatoes, add carrots; cook 1 to 2 minutes
Remove carrots, add bell peppers; cook 30 to 40 seconds
Remove bell peppers, add onions, garlic, ginger; cook until soft
Add chicken; cook until browned
Add fish sauce; cook 1 minute
Add coconut milk and water; bring to simmer, skim scum
Lower heat, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes
Add potatoes and carrots; cook 3 to 5 minutes
Add curry powder, stir to combine; cook 2 to 3 minutes
Season with salt and pepper to taste
Add bell peppers and cook 1 minutes
